result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin W. Domke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 3:13 p.m. Defendant Dustin W. Domke in court.  Defendant is now working - can pay in full within 1-1/2 months  Review hearing scheduled for March 14, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

2:01 p.m. Defendant Dustin W. Domke in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Plea questionnaire filed. Defendant enters no contest plea.  Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. State complied with victim rights. Voorhees/Schiek/Court statement to sentencing.  Court imposes $579 fine (Including costs).  Review hearing scheduled for December 14, 2015 at 03:00 pm. Adj. 2:10 p.m.
States Reply to Discovery  and State's Demand for Discovery

02:28 pm - Defendant Dustin W. Domke in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In receipt of complaint, waive reading - not guilty plea 
Bail continued  Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 15, 2015 at 02:00 pm.

03:55 pm - Defendant Dustin W. Domke in court.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court questions defendant as to obtaining counsel.  Defendant states has not contacted PD.  States has two jobs.  Defendant requests additional time to obtain counsel.  Court will grant one more adjournment.  Bail continued.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for July 20, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

01:31 pm - Defendant Dustin W. Domke in court, via video, in custody.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In receipt of complaint, right to counsel - defendant unsure as to obtaining counsel.  Schiek statement to bail - Court sets $ sig bond.  Defendant provides an address of W4152 Kline Road, Bryant, WI 54418 - Living with father.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for June 22, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
